WEBVTT

00:16.080 --> 00:21.260
A preface to the first edition of Jane Eyre being unnecessary, I gave none.

00:21.820 --> 00:26.600
This second edition demands a few words, both of acknowledgement and miscellaneous remark.

00:27.520 --> 00:32.780
My thanks are due in three quarters. To the public for the indulgent ear it has inclined

00:32.780 --> 00:38.680
to a plain tale with few pretensions. To the press for the fair field its honest suffrage

00:38.680 --> 00:45.580
has opened to an obscure aspirant. To my publishers for the aid their tact, their energy,

00:45.700 --> 00:51.380
their practical sense, and frank liberality have afforded to an unknown and un-recommended author.

00:52.200 --> 00:57.540
The press and the public are vague personifications for me and I must thank them in vague terms.

00:58.020 --> 01:02.140
But my publishers are definite so they are certain generous critics who have encouraged

01:02.140 --> 01:07.640
me as only large-hearted and high-minded men know how to encourage a struggling stranger.

01:08.200 --> 01:15.060
To them, i.e. to my publishers and select reviewers, I say cordially, gentlemen, I thank

01:15.060 --> 01:19.940
you from my heart. Having thus acknowledged what I owe to those who have aided and approved

01:19.940 --> 01:26.360
me, I turn to another class, a small one so far as I know, but not, therefore, to be overlooked.

01:26.860 --> 01:32.780
I mean the timorous or carpian few who doubt the tendency of such books as Jane Eyre, in

01:32.780 --> 01:39.380
whose eyes whatever is unusual is wrong, whose ears detect in each protest against bigotry,

01:39.760 --> 01:46.460
that parent of crime and insult to piety, that region of God on earth. I would suggest

01:46.460 --> 01:53.720
to such doubters certain obvious distinctions. I would remind them of simple truths. Conventionality

01:53.720 --> 02:00.260
is not morality. Self-righteousness is not religion. To attack the first is not to assail

02:00.260 --> 02:05.660
the last. To pluck the mask from the face of the Pharisee is not to lift an impious

02:05.660 --> 02:11.740
hand to the crown of thorns. These things and deeds are diametrically opposed. They

02:11.740 --> 02:18.520
are as distinct as advice from virtue. Men too often confound them. They should not be

02:18.520 --> 02:24.220
confounded. Appearance should not be mistaken for truth. Narrow human doctrines that only

02:24.220 --> 02:29.120
tend to elate and magnify a few should not be substituted for the world-redeeming creed

02:29.120 --> 02:36.200
of Christ. There is, I repeat it, a difference, and it is good, and not a bad action, to mark

02:36.200 --> 02:41.720
broadly and clearly the line of separation between them. The world may not like to see

02:41.720 --> 02:47.180
these ideas dissevered, for it has been accustomed to blend them, finding it convenient to make

02:47.180 --> 02:53.280
external show pass for sterling worth, to let whitewashed walls vouch for clean shrines.

02:53.500 --> 02:59.080
It may hate him who declares to scrutinize and expose, to raise the gilding and show

02:59.080 --> 03:05.440
base material under it, to penetrate the sepulcher and reveal carnal relics, but hate as it will,

03:05.440 --> 03:12.200
it is indebted to him. Ahab did not like Micaiah, because he never prophesied good concerning him,

03:12.340 --> 03:19.880
but evil. Probably he liked the sufferant son, Cheniah, better, yet Ahab have escaped a bloody

03:19.880 --> 03:26.340
death had he but stopped his ears to flattery, and opened them to faithful counsel. There is

03:26.340 --> 03:31.540
a man in our own days whose words are not framed to tickle delicate ears, who, to my thinking,

03:31.540 --> 03:37.500
comes before the great ones of society, much as the son of Imla came before the throned kings of

03:37.500 --> 03:43.660
Judah and Israel, and who speaks as deep, with a powerful, a prophet-like, a vital, as mean and

03:43.660 --> 03:50.320
dauntless and as daring. Is a satirist of vanity fair admired in high places? I cannot tell. But

03:50.320 --> 03:56.140
I think of some of those amongst whom he hurls the Greek fire of his sarcasm, and over whom he

03:56.140 --> 04:01.820
flashes the leavened brand of his denunciation, where to take his warnings in time, they or their

04:01.820 --> 04:09.160
seed might yet escape a fatal rimloth Gilead. Why have I alluded to this man? I have alluded to him,

04:09.160 --> 04:15.540
reader, because I think I see in him an intellect profounder and more unique than his contemporaries

04:15.540 --> 04:21.780
have yet recognized, because I regard him as the first social regenerator of the day, as the very

04:21.780 --> 04:27.680
master of that working core who would restore to rectitude the warped system of things, because I

04:27.680 --> 04:33.200
think no commentator on his writings has yet found the comparison that suits him, the terms which

04:33.200 --> 04:39.340
rightly characterize his talent. They say he is like Fielding, they talk of his wit, humor, comic

04:39.340 --> 04:45.660
powers. He resembles Fielding as an eagle does a vulture. Fielding could stoop on a carrion,

04:45.820 --> 04:51.760
but Thackerley never does. His wit is bright, his humor is attractive, but both bear the same

04:51.760 --> 04:56.780
relation to his serious genius that mere lambient sheet lightning playing under the edge of the

04:56.780 --> 05:03.840
summer cloud does to the electric death-spark hid in its womb. Finally, I have alluded to Mr. Thackerley,

05:03.920 --> 05:09.340
because to him, if he will accept the tribute of a total stranger, I have dedicated this second

05:09.340 --> 05:16.160
edition of Jane Eyre, Courier-Belle, Dec. 21, 1847.

05:17.440 --> 05:23.400
Note to the third edition. I avail myself of this opportunity, which a third edition of Jane Eyre

05:23.400 --> 05:29.420
affords me, of again addressing a word to the public, to exclaim that my claim to the title of

05:29.420 --> 05:35.660
novelist rests on this one work alone. If, therefore, the authorship of other works of

05:35.660 --> 05:41.180
fiction has been attributed to me, an honor is awarded where it is not merited, and consequently

05:41.180 --> 05:47.040
denied where it is justly due. This explanation will serve to rectify mistakes which have already

05:47.040 --> 05:54.140
been made and to prevent future errors. Courier-Belle, April 13, 1848.

